Role Description
This is a full-time on-site role for a Land Acquisition Executive based in Chennai. The Land Acquisition Executive will be responsible for managing land acquisition processes, negotiating land deals, conducting property research, and maintaining relationships with landowners and real estate agents.

Responsibilities
•	Identify and evaluate potential acquisition opportunities.
•	Conduct market and property research to inform acquisition strategies.
•	Negotiate and execute purchase agreements.
•	Manage due diligence processes, including title reviews and environmental assessments.
•	Develop and maintain relationships with property owners, brokers, and other stakeholders.
•	Prepare reports and presentations for senior management and stakeholders.
•	Stay up to date on industry trends, regulations, and best practices.
•	Providing leadership.
•	Inspecting private property.
•	Serving as members of a preliminary engineering team.
