Land acquisition analyst
•	Prepares market analysis reports to assess property values, finds potential land purchases, and evaluates the cost and benefits of the purchase.

Land acquisition executive
•	Finds new land for companies to buy, conducts land analysis, market research, and feasibility reports, negotiates land acquisition contracts, and processes applications and permits.

General land acquisition
•	Identifies large blocks of land, authenticates registered property title documents, reads agreements and sale deeds, initiates discussions with government departments, obtains land records, gathers details of legal heirs and outstanding liabilities, mitigates legal risks, coordinates with advocates, gives suggestions and opinions to management, and provides support to the site team.

